 but there is tons of high lvl content that is always open in other zones.<br>
<br>
i am a lvl 36 shaodwblade and here is my veiwpoint on rogues.<br>
<br>
in RvR level is king. as someone said one level makes a big diffrence. on average i kill any yellow con and under and lose to any orange con and over. thats when one on one. <br>
<br>
for XP items make the world of diffrence. the better your weapons and armor the more usefull and succesful you will be<br>
<br>
as far as groups. i have noticed a trend and that is small groups consisting of this situation. a 2 person group-one healer and one warrior. if you notice almost always the highest lvl people on the servers will be healers and warriors. <br>
<br>
if your a shadowblade and your looking for a pickup group pick out your best book and start reading because you will be bypassed if any other class is LFG. shadowblades are at the bottom of the barrel for being chosen for groups. most groups would rather just not add another person than add a shadowblade. it's too bad because in small groups shadowblades actualy can be of benefit. <br>
<br>
in solo RvR its almost impossible to kill a patient shadowblade. only time i am killed in RvR is when i am grouped with other people or i am ready to log or looking for a free ride back to my bind spot. the exception can be traps. a patient archer can find good assasin marks and just wait for me. but night time is always a friend of the shadowblade. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
                                     flea bitten <br>
                                     lvl 36 shadowblade<br>
